==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: markweed
<hw>markweed</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A climbing plant
(<spn>Toxicodendron radicans</spn>) common in eastern and central U. S.
with ternate leaves and greenish flowers followed by white berries. It
yields an irritating oil that causes a rash on contact; commonly called
<altname>poison ivy</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> poison ivy, poison mercury, poison oak,
<spn>Toxicodendron radicans</spn>, <spn>Rhus radicans</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marl</ent>⟦br⟧
